{color:#172B4D}Hi Team, I wanted to take a moment to introduce myself. I’m Marlon Bermudez, and I’m serving as the CISO at Ceres Life. I’m here to help lead and grow our Cybersecurity and Compliance program as we continue building a strong and trusted organization.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

{color:#172B4D} I know everyone has been working incredibly hard to get things ready, and I appreciate the focus and momentum across the company. Behind the scenes, I’ve been reviewing our current security posture and identifying ways we can strengthen our cybersecurity foundation to support Ceres Life as we scale.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

{color:#172B4D} To support that effort, we’ve launched a new{color} [{color:#172B4D} Information Security{color}|https://3clife.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/IS/overview]{color:#172B4D} space in Confluence. This will be our central hub for company-wide security updates, guidance, and awareness resources. Please see a{color} [{color:#172B4D} security advisory on scams via text messages{color}|https://3clife.atlassian.net/wiki/x/BgB_CQ]{color:#172B4D} we should all be aware of. Thanks.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

{color:#172B4D} If you ever come across something suspicious, whether it is a strange email, text, or anything else that does not feel right, please report it to security@ceresinsurance.com so we can take a look.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

{color:#172B4D} I’m excited to collaborate with all of you as we continue building a culture that supports growth and innovation.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

{color:#172B4D} Thanks, and I look forward to working together.{color}{color:#172B4D}{color}  

